Package net.dean.jraw.models

Contains models used in JRAW

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Created
    Indicates that this Thing was created
    Distinguishable
    Indicates this Thing can be posted by a redditor of elevated privilege
    Votable
    Provides a way to show that this Thing is able to be voted on
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Captcha
    Represents a Captcha.
    EmbeddedMedia
    This class represents a simplified version of oEmbed data that includes embedded HTML
    Flair
    Represents the flair of either an author or a submission
    JsonModel
    This class provides an abstract model for retrieving data from a JSON node, although not necessarily relating to the Reddit API.
    LoggedInAccount  
    LoggedInAccount.SubmissionBuilder
    This class provides a way to configure posting parameters of a new submission
    MultiReddit
    Represents a collection of subreddits.
    OEmbed
    Represents media provided by an oEmbed-style JSON object.
    OEmbed.Thumbnail
    Represents an oEmbed thumbnail
    RedditObject
    Provides another layer of abstraction between "normal" models (as seen here) like Submission and "abnormal" models like Listing and More.
    RenderStringPair
    This class represents a String that has a raw, unformatted version in Markdown, and a formatted version in HTML.
    WikiPage
    Represents a wiki page.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    DistinguishedState
    Represents the status of a link poster.
    OEmbed.MediaType
    The type of media that this OEmbed object represents
    ThingType
    An enumeration of types of objects in Reddit's API.
    VoteDirection
    Represents the way a user can vote on a Submission or Comment
  • Annotation Types Summary 
    Annotation Type Description
    JsonInteraction
    Used for testing purposes to signify that this method interacts with the JSON response in order to provide a usable API in pure Java.
